Can I define a class name on paragraph using Markdown? (https://stackoverflow.com/a/49697482)
(https://kramdown.gettalong.org/syntax.html#attribute-list-definitions)
If your flavour of markdown is kramdown, then you can set css class like this:

{:.nameofclass .anotherClass}
paragraph is here


<div> with markdown
In many (most?) varietals of Markdown, you can put <div markdown="1"> on the element and it will allow Markdown inside of it.
(https://css-tricks.com/little-stuff-markdown-always-forget-google/#article-header-id-0)

<div class="special-class" markdown="1">
    1. All
    1. Fixed 
    1. Up
</div>


Adding ids to headers:
(https://css-tricks.com/little-stuff-markdown-always-forget-google/#article-header-id-3)
### Custom IDs {#custom-id}


When you want to highlight a message:
Use the class "message"
<div class="message message-compressed float-right">

When you want to highligh a quoted text in a conversation like quotings:
<span class="quoted-text">
examples:
/2017/04/27/dr-jason-lisle-facebook-post-on-induction/
/2019/06/29/steven-van-deursen-on-async-await/

